{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 19:20:25.502265", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Solution submitted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"pc_0_0\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"link_down\"]\n\nRecommendation (next steps you can perform outside of this submission):\n- On pc_0_0:\n  - Bring the interface up: sudo ip link set dev eth0 up (or use ifconfig up).\n  - Check dmesg / system logs for NIC errors or driver issues.\n  - Verify cable/virtual link and link lights if physically accessible.\n- On leaf_router_0_0:\n  - Optionally check interface counters: show interfaces eth8, check RX/TX, errors.\n  - Attempt ping from leaf_router_0_0 to 10.0.0.2 to confirm reachability once host interface is up.\n- If interface repeatedly goes down, inspect NIC drivers, virtualization host (if VM), or replace cable/port.\n\nIf you want, I can run the targeted checks you suggested (leaf interface counters, LLDP, ping from leaf to host) to further confirm specifics.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1862, "output_tokens": 223, "total_tokens": 2085, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
